  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "There are numerous places where we use ADDR in the proxy middleware, and I'm adding a new one in teh caching middleware. ADDR is a IP:PORT number, but in some places we also allow a file structured like `/etc/resolv` to be used; CoreDNS will use the nameservers in there.\r\n\r\nWe should unify all these places and make it obvious that anywhere you can use ADDR you should also be able to use a file specifier.\r\n\r\n*May* be suitable for a beginner.",
